Latte Lane is a Java-based point-of-sale (POS)
application created for a custom coffee shop.
The application allows customers to place and
customize coffee orders through a menu-driven console interface.
Customers can order coffee drinks in different sizes, add premium
and regular add-ins, order pastries and other drinks,
review their order, and generate receipt files automatically.

This project was built using Object-Oriented Programming
principles and demonstrates concepts such as encapsulation,
polymorphism, inheritance, interfaces, builder patterns,
collections, loops, file handling, and separation of concerns.